Three agents — a yard operator who dispatches the inbound and outbound robotic trucks, a logistics planner who holds the shift manifest and the stack layout, and a crane operator who holds the physical yard map and executes one physical crane move per tool call — coordinate over a shared link channel to place one to three incoming containers into their correct slots each round across {{ round_count }} rounds. Customs inspectors are waiting at each target slot: every container must reach its slot within a fixed {{ time_budget_seconds }}-second inspection window or the inspection is missed and the round fails. Every character sent on the link channel costs one simulated second against that window.

The yard operator sees each incoming container's ID one at a time and only learns the next ID after the previous container has been placed. They do not see the yard map or the manifest, so they cannot decide on their own which station or pad to dispatch a truck to. The logistics planner sees the current four-stack layout and the shift manifest of scheduled inbound containers paired with their target slots, but does NOT see which crane stations are active or which stacks each station reaches; the planner converts a container ID into a target slot ``(stack, tier)`` and the ordered crane plan. The crane operator alone sees the round's physical yard map: which crane stations are active, the two transfer pads at each station, and which stacks each station can reach. The crane operator turns the planner's target slot into a dispatch order to the yard operator (``station_name`` + ``pad`` per truck) and then executes the planner's crane plan. Some deliveries need a buried-slot reshuffle: one blocker container must be lifted onto a separate outbound truck (which leaves loaded) before the inbound truck's container can be placed.

Round success requires every scheduled delivery to complete with its expected trucks (the inbound truck always; the outbound truck whenever the target slot is already occupied, arriving empty), every expected crane move executed in the right order by the right container, and the inspection window not exhausted.
